{
  "version": 1,
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "RQ-0008",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Fix machine run loop idle and blocked summaries",
      "description": "Repair the machine contract for `ralph machine run loop` so idle, no-candidate, blocked, stalled, stopped, failed, and completed states remain distinct all the way to terminal machine summaries and RalphMac Run Control. Today several non-success operator states return `Ok(())` from the shared loop implementation and the machine command emits `outcome: \"completed\"` with no `blocking`, which lets the Swift app clear or hide useful operator state. The desired outcome is a loop-level outcome model with blocking-aware summaries that match the semantics already expected from `machine run one`.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "machine-api",
        "run-loop",
        "ralphmac",
        "blocking",
        "ux"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/run.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_loop/orchestration.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/blocking.rs",
        "crates/ralph/tests/machine_contract_test/",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+MachineOutput.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/WorkspaceRunStateResumeBlockingTests.swift",
        "docs/machine-contract.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/run.rs` emits a hardcoded loop terminal summary with `outcome: \"completed\"` and `blocking: None` after `run_loop(...)` succeeds.",
        "`crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_loop/orchestration.rs` returns `Ok(())` for no initial todo tasks, no runnable candidates, and blocked tasks when not waiting.",
        "`apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+MachineOutput.swift` clears live blocking when a terminal run summary has no blocking payload.",
        "Live probe on an empty initialized repo emitted `run_started`, `resume_decision`, then `{\"version\":2,\"task_id\":null,\"exit_code\":0,\"outcome\":\"completed\"}` while stderr said `No todo tasks found.`"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce a loop outcome model that distinguishes completed, no-candidates, blocked, stalled, stopped, and failed outcomes instead of collapsing them into `Ok(())`.",
        "Update `machine run loop` to build terminal `MachineRunSummaryDocument` values from the loop outcome, including canonical `BlockingState` when the run is idle, blocked, or stalled.",
        "Update RalphMac run-summary application so a generic terminal summary cannot clear useful live blocking state unless the summary explicitly supersedes it.",
        "Add Rust machine-contract tests for empty queue, blocked queue, and no-candidate loop summaries, plus Swift state-reduction tests proving Run Control preserves actionable blocking state.",
        "Update `docs/machine-contract.md` examples for loop summaries and blocking outcomes."
      ],
      "request": "update the .ralph/queue.jsonc with tasks to remediate every finding.",
      "created_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [
        "RQ-0009"
      ],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "audit_finding": "HIGH: machine run loop reports idle and blocked states as completed",
        "source_report": "/tmp/ralph-report.md"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "RQ-0009",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Guarantee terminal machine summaries for loop failures",
      "description": "Make `ralph machine run loop` emit a deterministic terminal machine summary on recoverable execution failures instead of short-circuiting through `?` after structured start events. Native clients should not have to infer final run state from process exit, stderr, or human text after the machine stream begins.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "machine-api",
        "run-loop",
        "errors",
        "contracts",
        "ralphmac"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/run.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_loop/orchestration.rs",
        "crates/ralph/tests/machine_contract_test/",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+Execution.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+MachineOutput.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/WorkspaceRunCancelAndLoopTests.swift",
        "docs/machine-contract.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/run.rs` calls `run_loop(...)?` and only emits the terminal `MachineRunSummaryDocument` on success.",
        "`emit_run_summary` already maps one-shot run outcomes and errors into machine summaries, but the loop path does not use an equivalent result-to-summary path.",
        "RalphMac has subprocess exit handling and raw stderr/stdout capture, but the app contract expects versioned machine documents rather than human prose."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Build on the loop outcome work from RQ-0008 so loop execution returns enough structured detail to summarize both success and failure.",
        "Wrap machine loop execution in a result-to-summary path that emits `machine_error` plus a terminal summary for recoverable runtime failures after machine mode starts.",
        "Classify startup failures that occur before a machine stream can be established separately from in-stream loop failures.",
        "Add contract tests proving runner failure during loop still produces a terminal machine summary with exit code, outcome, and blocking/stalled context where appropriate.",
        "Update RalphMac tests so loop failure state is driven by machine documents rather than raw stderr interpretation."
      ],
      "request": "update the .ralph/queue.jsonc with tasks to remediate every finding.",
      "created_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "depends_on": [
        "RQ-0008"
      ],
      "blocks": [],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "audit_finding": "HIGH: machine run loop does not guarantee a terminal machine summary on error paths",
        "source_report": "/tmp/ralph-report.md"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "RQ-0010",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Let machine run one select the next task for RalphMac",
      "description": "Remove RalphMac's duplicated next-task selection before `machine run one`. The app currently reads the queue, chooses a task ID, then invokes `machine run one --id <id>`, which can race external queue changes and drift from CLI selection rules. When the user clicks Run Next without an explicit task selection, the app should call no-ID `ralph machine run one --resume` and render the actual selected task from machine output.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "ralphmac",
        "machine-api",
        "queue",
        "race",
        "ux"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+Execution.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+MachineOutput.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/WorkspaceRunCancelAndLoopTests.swift",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/run.rs",
        "crates/ralph/tests/machine_contract_test/"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController.swift` resolves a task ID in the app before invoking `machine run one --id <id>`.",
        "`apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+Execution.swift` calls `machine queue read` and falls back to local `workspace.nextTask()` for run selection.",
        "The Rust machine command already supports no-ID selection through canonical CLI queue logic."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Change RalphMac Run Next so the default no-explicit-selection path invokes `ralph machine run one --resume` without `--id`.",
        "Keep app-side queue reads for display/previews only, not command shaping.",
        "Ensure machine output carries enough selected-task detail for the app to update the current task after CLI-side selection.",
        "Add a test that simulates stale app queue state and verifies the CLI still selects the canonical current next task.",
        "Preserve explicit selected-task runs by passing `--id` only when the user intentionally selected a specific task."
      ],
      "request": "update the .ralph/queue.jsonc with tasks to remediate every finding.",
      "created_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "audit_finding": "MEDIUM: app-side Run Next Task duplicates CLI task selection and can race",
        "source_report": "/tmp/ralph-report.md"
      }
