    {
      "id": "RQ-0011",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Move Stop After Current onto a machine command",
      "description": "Replace RalphMac's Stop After Current implementation that shells out to human `ralph queue stop` with a typed machine command and versioned document. Stopping a loop is an operator-critical workflow, so the app should receive structured status, resolved paths, marker state, continuation context, and machine-safe errors instead of parsing or appending raw stdout/stderr.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "ralphmac",
        "machine-api",
        "run-loop",
        "stop",
        "ux"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/args.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/run.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/queue.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/queue/",
        "crates/ralph/tests/machine_contract_test/",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+Execution.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/WorkspaceRunCancelAndLoopTests.swift",
        "docs/machine-contract.md",
        "docs/features/app.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+Execution.swift` invokes `ralph queue stop` for Stop After Current.",
        "The app captures raw stdout/stderr and appends warning prose on failure.",
        "`docs/features/app.md` says native workflows should use machine-readable JSON/structured outputs instead of human CLI text."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add a machine command such as `ralph machine run stop` or `ralph machine queue stop` for stop-marker preview/apply behavior.",
        "Define and document a versioned stop document containing status, resolved queue/done paths, marker action, continuation/blocking context, and machine-safe error details.",
        "Update RalphMac Stop After Current to consume only the new machine document.",
        "Remove raw stdout/stderr based stop-state interpretation from the native workflow.",
        "Add Rust contract tests and Swift tests for created, already-present, and failed stop-marker states."
      ],
      "request": "update the .ralph/queue.jsonc with tasks to remediate every finding.",
      "created_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-26T00:04:48Z",
